sys_update_xml.name: sysevent_in_email_action_6757dba7c3123100d5907bfaa2d3aec3
sys_update_xml.payload:
record_actiontrue((new CSEMailUtil).checkCaseProperty(email.to)) && ((new CSEMailUtil).isUserExist(email.from))This inbound email action is triggered when an email is sent to ServiceNow and: 1. The email is not a reply or forward. 2. The send to address is the same as the address configed in Customer Service -> Administration -> Email Properties: Case email address This inbound email action can set the following fields on a new case: contact short_description description channel account product In addition to being able to explicitly set the values of the above fields within the email, the following is done automatically: 1. The Case contact is set to the sender, if the sender's email is registered. 2. The email subject is set as the Case short description. 3. The whole email is set as the Case description. 4. The Case channel is set to "email". 5. The Case account is set to the sender's account, if the sender has correct account. 6. The Case product is set if the email subject has correct format and contains the correct product name. [product display name: title] Example email: This email will create a new Case with the following: 1. The Case contact is set to "Fred Luddy". 2. The Case short description will be set to "Router1122: Not able to connect to wireless network". 3. The Case description will be set to the whole email body. 4. The Case channel is set to "email" 5. The Case account is set to the correct account 6. The Case product will be set to "Router1122" ----- From: Fred Luddy <fred.luddy@example.com> Subject: Router1122: Not able to connect to wireless network Date: June 11, 2013 1:44:55 PM PDT To: ServiceNow The wireless network has been down for 30 minutes now. assign: Bow Ruggeri -----email.readCreate Case via property50truesysevent_in_email_actionadmin2015-02-24 06:19:02global/6757dba7c3123100d5907bfaa2d3aec343Create Case via property51d811fad7223100b7490ee60e61034f51d811fad7223100b7490ee60e61034fsysevent_in_email_action_6757dba7c3123100d5907bfaa2d3aec3tim_deniston2019-05-20 14:34:00sn_customerservice_case

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_ad6d02abdbbae300bd00f8ecbf961983
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>sn_customerservice.getAccountsProducts</api_name><client_callable>true</client_callable><description/><name>getAccountsProducts</name><script><![CDATA[function getAccountsProducts(account) {
	if (!account.nil()) {
		var query = new GlideRecord('u_m2m_product_account');
		query.addQuery('u_account', account);
		query.query();

		var ans = [];

		while(query.next()) {
			ans.push(query.getValue('u_product'));
		}
		
		var children = [];
		
		for (var i in ans) {
			var childQuery = new GlideRecord('cmdb_m2m_suite_model');
			childQuery.addQuery('suite_parent', ans[i]);
			childQuery.query();
			
			while (childQuery.next()) {
				children.push(childQuery.getValue('suite_child'));
			}
		}
		
		var joinedArray = ans.concat(children);
		
		return 'sys_idIN' + joinedArray.join();
	}
}]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>tim_deniston</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-01-10 18:48:06</sys_created_on><sys_id>ad6d02abdbbae300bd00f8ecbf961983</sys_id><sys_mod_count>6</sys_mod_count><sys_name>getAccountsProducts</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Customer Service" source="sn_customerservice">51d811fad7223100b7490ee60e61034f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Customer Service">51d811fad7223100b7490ee60e61034f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_ad6d02abdbbae300bd00f8ecbf961983</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>tim_deniston</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-01-25 16:22:09</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
